public class Edge<T>

    • equals

      public boolean equals​(Edge<T> other)
      Checks if given edge is equal. If the edge is directed then the edge is only equal if the two vertices are equal. Otherwise if the edge is not directed then edge is equal if the two points in the edge are equal.
      Parameters:
      other - edge to check if equals
      Returns:
      true if the edges are equal
